		<td><b>Active Low SLROM</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I am trying to make a repro cartridge and I had a basic question. I am using a SLROM donor board and for the PRG rom and I am using a 28 pin Dip 27c512. The mask rom and the eprom are nearly pin compatiable with the only different being pin 22. The eprom has this as /CE (active low?) and the mask rom has pin 22 listed as A16. 
<br />
<br />My question is what am I supposed to do at this point. Will this work as is or do I have to do something? I have seen the pin conversion for the eproms, but those refer to 32 pin eproms and I am using a 28 pin so I am confused about using the right chip or not.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

